text: Bonneville County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 123,964 people lived there, making it the fourth-most populous county in Idaho and the most populous in eastern Idaho. Its county seat and largest city is Idaho Falls. == Communities == === Cities === * Ammon * Idaho Falls * Iona * Irwin * Ririe (partially) * Swan Valley * Ucon === Census-designated place === * Lincoln === Unincorporated communities === * Beachs Corner * Bone * Osgood * Palisades === Ghost towns === * Herman * Caribou City == References == Category:1911 establishments in Idaho Category:Idaho counties
